'''Tshepang Moremi''' (born 2 October 2000) is a South African [[association football|soccer]] player who plays as a winger for [[Premier Soccer League]] club [[Orlando Pirates F.C.|Orlando Pirates]] and the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]].

== Club career ==
Moremi was an academy player at Sharpeville Benfica.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://farpost.co.za/2022/09/27/benni-mccarthys-prodigy-on-why-he-will-succeed-at-manchester-united/|title=Benni McCarthy's prodigy on why he will succeed at Manchester United|date=27 September 2022|publisher=FAR Post|access-date=27 March 2024}}</ref> He joined [[AmaZulu F.C.|AmaZulu]] after playing for the [[Bizana Pondo Chiefs F.C.|Bizana Pondo Chiefs]]. He made his debut in the [[2021-22 South African Premier Division]] in August against Mamelodi Sundowns, and scored his first goal in December against Kaizer Chiefs. He spent the 2022–23 season on loan at [[JDR Stars F.C.|JDR Stars]]. After he returned, he played all AmaZulu's games. In late 2023 and early 2024, rumours arose that South African giants Mamelodi Sundowns and Orlando Pirates were interested in Moremi. AmaZulu had the opportunity to place a high price tag on Moremi, should other clubs want to buy the player.<ref>{{soccerway|tshepang-moremi/685668}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://farpost.co.za/2023/12/21/pablo-franco-reacts-to-moremis-links-with-pirates-and-sundowns/|title=Pablo Franco reacts to Moremi's links with Pirates and Sundowns|date=21 December 2023|author=Sithole, Sinethemba|publisher=FAR Post|access-date=27 March 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.snl24.com/soccerladuma/local/siyagobhoza/moremi-amazulu-set-price-tag-for-orlando-pirates-mamelodi-sundowns-target-20240307|title=AmaZulu Set High Price Tag For Pirates & Downs Target|date=7 March 2024|publisher=Soccer Laduma|access-date=27 March 2024}}</ref>

=== Orlando Pirates ===
In July 2025 he joined [[Premier Soccer League]] club [[Orlando Pirates F.C.|Orlando Pirates]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Dube |first=Mthokozisi |date=2025-07-26 |title=Tshepang Moremi: From the athletics tracks of Sharpeville to Orlando Pirates |url=https://farpost.co.za/2025/07/26/moremi-from-the-athletics-tracks-of-sharpeville-to-pirates/ |access-date=2025-09-13 |website=FARPost |language=en-ZA}}</ref> He scored a brace in extra time to help Pirates to a 3–0 win over [[Stellenbosch F.C.|Stellenbosch]] in the [[2025 MTN 8]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=2025-09-13 |title=History for Orlando Pirates! Super-subs Tshepang Moremi and Tshegofatso Mabasa lead the Buccaneers to fourth-consecutive MTN8 title with victory over Stellenbosch {{!}} Goal.com South Africa |url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/lists/history-for-orlando-pirates-super-subs-tshepang-moremi-and-tshegofatso-mabasa-lead-the-buccaneers-to-fourth-consecutive-mtn8-title-with-victory-over-stellenbosch/bltceee4d32d3a2fb06 |access-date=2025-09-13 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-ZA}}</ref>

== International career ==
In late 2023, Moremi was called up to [[Bafana Bafana]] by [[Hugo Broos]] as part of a 50-man preliminary squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.citizen.co.za/sport/soccer/local-soccer/bafana-broos-50-man-preliminary-afcon-squad/|title=Bafana's Broos names 50-man preliminary Afcon squad|last=Mark|first=Jonty|date=14 December 2023|publisher=The Citizen|access-date=27 March 2024}}</ref> He was again in the preliminary squad for the [[2024 FIFA Series]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.news24.com/citypress/sport/bafana-coach-hugo-broos-takes-new-approach-with-fresh-faces-20240310|title=Bafana coach Hugo Broos takes new approach with fresh faces|last=Malepa|first=Tiisetso|date=10 March 2024|publisher=City Press|access-date=27 March 2024}}</ref> In 2024 he finally made his Bafana Bafana debut, coming on as a substitute in South Africa's first [[2024 COSAFA Cup]] game.<ref>{{NFT player|95265}}</ref>

On 1 December 2025, Moremi was called up to the South Africa squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/totalenergies-afcon-morocco-2025-fever-rises-as-broos-become-first-coach-to-unveil-final-squad/|title=TotalEnergies AFCON Morocco 2025 fever rises as Broos become first coach to unveil final squad|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=1 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

